$ Windows Settings: Region & language

The *Region & language* settings Window can be opened on the command line with
code {
c:\> start ms-settings:regionlanguage
code }

gh|Windows-Pics|/ms-settings/regionlanguage/main.png||

{ Country or region

  The chosen value of *Country or region* is stored in the → Windows/registry under the key
  → Windows/registry/tree/HKEY_CURRENT_USER/Control-Panel/International/Geo[`HKEY_CURRENT_USER\Control Panel\International\Geo`].


  With → Windows/PowerShell, the value of *Country or region* can be set or queried with the noun
  → Windows/PowerShell/command-inventory/noun/winHomeLocation[`winHomeLocation`].

}
sa:

  → Windows/settings/Time-Language[Time & Language] related → Windows/settings[settings]

